sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Controller<br/>(modelmesh container)
    participant Puller as model-serving-puller<br/>8084/TCP gRPC plaintext
    participant Storage as Remote Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant FS as Local Filesystem<br/>/models
    participant Adapter as Runtime Adapter<br/>8085/TCP gRPC plaintext
    participant Server as Model Server<br/>8001/TCP gRPC plaintext

    Note over MM,Server: Flow 1: Model Loading

    MM->>Puller: loadModel(modelId, modelPath)<br/>gRPC :8084 plaintext
    Puller->>Puller: Parse storage-config Secret<br/>(mounted at /storage-config)
    Puller->>Storage: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS :443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Access Key / Azure AD / GCP SA
    Storage-->>Puller: Model artifacts (binary data)
    Puller->>FS: Write model files to /models/{modelId}
    Note over Puller,FS: Optional: Keras→TF conversion via tf_pb.py
    Puller->>Adapter: loadModel(modelId, localPath)<br/>gRPC :8085 plaintext
    Adapter->>Adapter: Adapt model layout for runtime<br/>(config generation, dir restructure)
    Adapter->>Server: Runtime-specific load API<br/>gRPC :8001 plaintext
    Server-->>Adapter: Load confirmation
    Adapter-->>Puller: ModelInfo (sizeInBytes)
    Puller-->>MM: loadModel response (success)

    Note over MM,Server: Flow 2: Model Unloading

    MM->>Puller: unloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC :8084 plaintext
    Puller->>Adapter: unloadModel(modelId)<br/>gRPC :8085 plaintext
    Adapter->>Server: Runtime-specific unload API<br/>gRPC :8001 plaintext
    Server-->>Adapter: Unload confirmation
    Adapter-->>Puller: Unload response
    Puller->>FS: Delete /models/{modelId}
    Puller-->>MM: unloadModel response (success)

    Note over MM,Server: Flow 3: Runtime Status Check

    MM->>Puller: runtimeStatus()<br/>gRPC :8084 plaintext
    Puller->>Adapter: runtimeStatus()<br/>gRPC :8085 plaintext
    Adapter->>Server: Health/status check<br/>gRPC :8001 plaintext
    Server-->>Adapter: Runtime capacity info
    Adapter-->>Puller: RuntimeStatusResponse
    Note over Puller: Purges stale models on startup
    Puller-->>MM: Status + capacity info
